                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony2-rest/edit/master/knpu/episode1/mad-test-debugging.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>When we mess up in a web app, we see Symfony's giant exception page. I want
that same experience when I'm building an API.</p>
<p>At the root of the project there's a <code>resources/</code> directory with an <code>ApiTestCase.php</code>
file. This has all the same stuff as <em>our</em> <code>ApiTestCase</code> plus some pretty
sweet new debugging stuff.</p>
<p>Copy this and paste it over our class.</p>
<p>First, check out <code>onNotSuccessfulTest()</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="7741babcf3">
